The 'Rhythm City' actor was held at gunpoint and later stuffed in the boot of his car before his car was taken. JOHANNESBURG Police are searching for three men who assaulted and hijacked actor Jamie Bartlett in Brixton near Auckland Park at the weekend. The Rhythm City actor was held at gunpoint and later stuffed in the boot of his car before his car was taken. Bartlett was also hit in the face before being thrown out in an open field in Zonkizizwe on the East Rand.The police s Kay Makhubele says: They drove with him away to an open space next to Zonkizizwe where he woke up and saw the house and he asked for help and the police were called. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)